The File Server is a service on the RING which provides a general filing
system service to other machines.  It is fully described in
     "FILE SERVER EXTERNAL SPECIFICATIONS"  by Jeremy Dion
                                         which is available in the lab.

For information about file server space accounting use HELP ACCOUNTING.

For information on a routine for finding which fileserver to talk to, given
a fileserver PUID, see HELP CALLSEG FIND-FILESERVER or
HELP SOURCELIB FIND-FILESERVER.


